N.Z. Economy Will Grow 2.2% in 2012, NZIER Consensus Survey Says

-- B y   C h r i s   B o u r k e
-- 
2011-12-11T23:00:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-11/n-z-economy-will-grow-2-2-in-2012-nzier-consensus-survey-says.html
New Zealand ’s economic recovery will
be slower than previously thought, according to the  New Zealand
Institute of Economic Research ’s Consensus Forecasts survey. The
economy will grow 2.2 percent in the year ending March 2012 and
growth will then rise to 3 percent in 2013 and 2014, economists
predicted in the e-mailed report. 